tables.table_schema:
CREATE TABLE customer_profiles (
  customer_id UUID PRIMARY KEY,
  name VARCHAR(50),
  email VARCHAR(100),
  age INT,
  gender VARCHAR(10),
  phone_number VARCHAR(20),
  credit_score INT
)

CREATE TABLE customer_profiles (
  customer_id INT PRIMARY KEY,
  full_name VARCHAR(50),
  age INT,
  email VARCHAR(100),
  phone_number VARCHAR(20)
);

CREATE TABLE preferences (
  preference_id INT PRIMARY KEY,
  customer_id INT,
  preference_type VARCHAR(50),
  preference_value TEXT,
  FOREIGN KEY (customer_id) REFERENCES customer_profiles(customer_id)
);

CREATE TABLE product_recommendations (
  recommendation_id INT PRIMARY KEY,
  customer_id INT,
  product_name VARCHAR(100),
  recommendation_score FLOAT,
  FOREIGN KEY (customer_id) REFERENCES customer_profiles(customer_id)
);

CREATE TABLE customer_profiles (
  customer_id INT PRIMARY KEY,
  first_name VARCHAR(50),
  last_name VARCHAR(50),
  email VARCHAR(100),
  phone_number VARCHAR(15),
  age INT,
  gender VARCHAR(10),
  income DECIMAL(10,2),
  created_at TIMESTAMP
)

CREATE TABLE preferences (
  preference_id INT PRIMARY KEY,
  customer_id INT,
  preference_name VARCHAR(50),
  preference_value VARCHAR(100),
  created_at TIMESTAMP,
  FOREIGN KEY (customer_id) REFERENCES customer_profiles(customer_id)
)

CREATE TABLE product_recommendations (
  recommendation_id INT PRIMARY KEY,
  customer_id INT,
  product_id INT,
  recommendation_score DECIMAL(10,2),
  created_at TIMESTAMP,
  FOREIGN KEY (customer_id) REFERENCES customer_profiles(customer_id),
  FOREIGN KEY (product_id) REFERENCES products(product_id)
)

CREATE TABLE products (
  product_id INT PRIMARY KEY,
  product_name VARCHAR(50),
  category VARCHAR(50),
  price DECIMAL(10,2),
  created_at TIMESTAMP
)

CREATE TABLE CustomerProfiles (
  id INT PRIMARY KEY,
  name VARCHAR(50),
  age INT,
  email VARCHAR(100),
  address VARCHAR(255)
)

CREATE TABLE Preferences (
  id INT PRIMARY KEY,
  customer_id INT,
  preference_category VARCHAR(50),
  preference_value VARCHAR(255)
)

CREATE TABLE ProductRecommendations (
  id INT PRIMARY KEY,
  product_id INT,
  customer_id INT,
  recommendation_score DECIMAL(5,2)
)

CREATE TABLE AIAlgorithms (
  id INT PRIMARY KEY,
  algorithm_name VARCHAR(50),
  description TEXT
)

CREATE TABLE FinancialProducts (
  id INT PRIMARY KEY,
  product_name VARCHAR(100),
  category VARCHAR(50),
  price DECIMAL(10,2)
)
